24:
You'll get there eventually, kid. Don't
sweat it.
28:
I've got a long way to go, but... Yeah,
I feel like I'm making progress, at
least.
33:
Well, that should about do it for
Claudius' request...
36:
Though I have some other business I
must attend to. I'll be making camp
here, but what of you two?
41:
Wouldn't make much sense to try
heading back now. We'll stick
around.
48:
Roast lizard again? Are you sure you
can stomach it, Teo?
53:
Oh, stuff it. Alk prepped some food
for us.
79: Huh? Why didn't you go before bed?
82:
You better not say you can't go by
yourself...
101: I guess this was her "other business."
118:
You're back there, aren't you? Come
on out.
123:
I'm sorry... I was just wondering what
you were doing out here...
127: Worried about me again, I see.
131:
There was once a catfolk settlement
just down from this hill.
135:
A settlement? Here? With all these
monsters crawling around?
139:
It was a village of assassins who
intended to murder the king of the
dogfolk.
148:
They're all gone now. Their blood is
on my hands.
153:
B-but Helga! It was a war, and you're
a warrior... You couldn't just leave
the assassins alone!
156:
Correct. I simply did what was
expected of a warrior, and I was
prepared for it.
159:
But even an assassin has a family
that cares about them.
172:
Who knows... But their eyes burned
with a desire for vengeance.
174:
And those children could very well
have grown up and faced me on the
battlefield many years later...
177:
Do you understand, Teo? Many
children became like Magnos
because of what I did.
185: Don't try to justify my actions, Teo.
189:
You mustn't let your sense of right
and wrong be twisted by trying to
affirm me.
198:
I didn't want him to know, but I
wonder if this is for the best.
202:
You sure like to talk like you know
everything.
210: Don't think so little of us.
217:
Sorry about this, Nimbus. I'll be
heading off now. Make sure you take
care of the little cub—
229: Don't treat me like some weak kid.
233:
You're my teacher, and nothing can
change what you mean to me.
242: You were the same as Magnos and I!
250:
But you still found me, and you
saved me!
254:
Do you really think I could just give
up on you because of your past?
259:
All right, Helga. I think you get the
picture now.
263: Yes, I do... and I'm sorry.
278: For seeing me for who I am now.
